<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-04-0251 </DOCNO><TEXT>The problem of the equivalence of the canonical and grand canonical ensemblesfor nonideal Bose systems is considered for the example of three exactlysolvable models, each of which undergoes a phase transition with theformation of a Bose condensate. It is shown that violation of the statistical(strong) equivalence of the ensembles is not a simple consequence ofBose condensation and equivalence is restored by changing the kind ofthe phase transition.</TEXT></DOC>